GPT-4V
GPT-4V is a large language model that excels in interpreting and reasoning over chart images, playing a critical role in ChartCitor.<SEP>GPT-4V is a variant of the GPT-4 model used for generating predictions related to bounding boxes and visual interpretation of data.<SEP>GPT-4V is an object detection method using Direct Bbox Decoding, scoring 12.5 IoU in the analysis.

Llama-3.2
Llama-3.2 is a large language model known for effective utilization of in-context learning and visual prompting.

Claude-3.5 Sonnet
Claude-3.5 Sonnet is another large language model capable of performing context-rich tasks including chart interpretation.

ChartCitor
ChartCitor is a multi-agent framework designed for providing fine-grained bounding box citations in chart question-answering tasks, enhancing the reliability and explainability of responses generated by large language models.<SEP>ChartCitor is a multimodal language model application used for converting data tables into visual charts and enabling complex visual tasks.<SEP>ChartCitor is a reasoning-based zero-shot segmentation model designed to generate masks from complex textual queries for visual chart understanding.<SEP>ChartCitor is a multi-agent framework designed for precise chart answer citations, featuring various interconnected agents for workflow optimization.<SEP>ChartCitor is an advanced system for object detection in chart images, achieving the highest IoU score of 27.4 among tested methods.<SEP>ChartCitor is a system being evaluated for its accuracy in comparison to GPT-4o, particularly regarding chart-based question answering.

Kanika Goswami
Kanika Goswami is affiliated with IGDTUW, Delhi, India, and is one of the authors of the work discussing ChartCitor.

Ryan Rossi
Ryan Rossi is associated with Adobe Research in the USA and contributed to the development of ChartCitor.

Puneet Mathur
Puneet Mathur works at Adobe Research in the USA and is a co-author of the paper on ChartCitor.<SEP>Puneet Mathur is a co-author working on multi-agent table structure attribution research.

Franck Dernoncourt
Franck Dernoncourt is part of Adobe Research in the USA and is one of the authors involved in the ChartCitor project.

Fine-grained Structured Chart Attribution
Fine-grained Structured Chart Attribution is a task that involves identifying graph elements supporting claims in text responses to user queries.

LLM Pre-filtering Agent
The LLM Pre-filtering Agent uses chain-of-thought prompting techniques to filter irrelevant rows and columns from tables.

Visual Fact Checking
Visual Fact Checking is a method used to verify the accuracy of information presented visually, especially in the context of chart data.

Information Systems
Information Systems refers to the discipline focused on the collection, organization, storage, and communication of information, playing a critical role in data extraction processes.

GPT-4o
GPT-4o is a language model utilized for various tasks including table cell captioning and evidence extraction.<SEP>GPT-4o is a system that is being compared to ChartCitor for its accuracy in processing chart-based questions.

LLM Re-ranking Agent
The LLM Re-ranking Agent is responsible for re-ranking extracted table cells to ensure they are relevant to answer claims.<SEP>The LLM Re-ranking Agent involves a selection process that improves the ranking of generated responses or answers.

Table Cell Retrieval
The Table Cell Retrieval event involves identifying relevant table cells through a two-step retrieval and ranking process.

Multimodal Retrieval
Multimodal Retrieval involves extracting information from multiple forms of media, including text, images, and charts, to enhance understanding and verification of data.

TabCite benchmark
The TabCite benchmark is a dataset used for evaluating performance in converting data tables into visual formats.

Kosmos-2
Kosmos-2 is a multimodal language model with text-to-visual grounding capabilities for generating bounding boxes.<SEP>Kosmos-2 is one of the tested models in the evaluation of visual chart understanding, known for its low performance in handling complex geometrical proportions.<SEP>Kosmos-2 is an object detection algorithm that scored 3.89 IoU, indicating limitations in handling complex visual reasoning tasks.

Visual Intersection over Union (IoU)
Visual Intersection over Union (IoU) is a metric used to evaluate the performance of chart attribution tasks.

ChatGPT
ChatGPT is the base multimodal language model employed in the ChartCitor project.

Captioning Agent
The Captioning Agent is responsible for describing the importance of each cell in the context of its associated row and column headers.

Cell Captioning
Cell Captioning is a process involving the generation of descriptions for individual cells in a table based on their context within rows and columns.

LISA
LISA is a reasoning-based model that generates segmentation masks from complex textual queries.<SEP>LISA is another tested model that performed poorly in the evaluation compared to ChartCitor, especially in terms of visual and numerical reasoning.<SEP>LISA is another object detection algorithm that scored 4.34 IoU, suggesting its inefficacy compared to advanced models.

Retrieve-then-rank approach
The Retrieve-then-rank approach is a method used to identify the most relevant table cells by first filtering then ranking them.

User Study
The user study involved participants evaluating the citation accuracy and perceived utility of fine-grained chart attribution provided by ChartCitor against GPT-4o.

LLM-based pre-filtering
LLM-based pre-filtering is a technique used to filter out irrelevant rows and columns to enhance the relevance of data retrieved.

Chart-Based Question Answering
Chart-based question answering refers to the process of generating answers based on data visualized in charts, evaluated in the context of user study.

Documentation on Chart Attribution
Documentation on chart attribution discusses the methodology and results related to the citations provided by different models in the study.

Participants
Participants in the user study evaluated 250 question-answer pairs and their associated chart images, contributing to the assessment of ChartCitor's effectiveness.

LLMs
LLMs refer to large language models that are used in various tasks, including generating answers to questions and providing citations.

Fine-Grained Chart Attribution
Fine-grained chart attribution relates to the detailed referencing and context provided for elements within charts used in data representation.

Bounding Boxes
Bounding boxes are rectangular areas used to identify and segment specific elements within visual data representations like charts.

The image is a diagram depicting the workflow of ChartCitor, a system for structured chart attribution. It visually breaks down the process into distinct agents: Table Extraction, Entity Captioning, Answer Reformulation, Prefiltering, Re-ranking, and Cell Localization, each linked in a logical, color-coded sequence geared towards providing detailed citations for chart data.

This table compares the IoU scores of various chart detection methods. ChartCitor leads with an IoU of 27.4, significantly outperforming others, thus illustrating the effectiveness of enhanced LLM techniques in visual data interpretation.

data.entity_name: Accuracy Comparison Bar Chart for ChartCitor and GPT-4o (image)
data.content: A bar chart visualizes the comparison of perceived accuracy between ChartCitor and GPT-4o in user evaluations. It shows higher complete accuracy for ChartCitor, while GPT-4o appears more often as completely inaccurate, reflecting the documented user study context for chart question-answering performance assessments.

Answer Reformulation Agent
The Answer Reformulation Agent breaks down answers into atomic facts for clarity and accuracy.

LLM Prefiltering Agent
The LLM Prefiltering Agent uses a score filter mechanism to assign relevance scores to rows and columns of data.

Table Extraction Agent
The Table Extraction Agent is a component of ChartCitor that processes input charts into HTML format using self-reflection and examples.

Score Filter
The Score Filter is a mechanism employed by the LLM Prefiltering Agent to assess the relevance of data rows and columns.

DETR
DETR is an object detection algorithm that, when combined with Set-of-Marks prompting, achieved an IoU score of 18.6.

Bounding Box Illustrations
Bounding Box Illustrations are visuals used by the Cell Localization Agent to represent mapped chart elements for identification.

Intersection over Union (IoU)
Intersection over Union (IoU) is a metric used to quantify the accuracy of object detection algorithms based on their predicted and ground truth bounding boxes.

Traditional Models
Traditional models refer to older object detection algorithms, such as Kosmos-2 and LISA, which exhibited lower performance in IoU metrics compared to more advanced techniques.

HTML Table
The HTML Table is a structured format for displaying tabular data, utilized by various agents in the ChartCitor framework.

Cell Localization Agent
The Cell Localization Agent utilizes 'DETR' for mapping elements of charts, aiding in accurate cell identification.

Entity Captioning Agent
The Entity Captioning Agent generates captions for different chart elements, such as row, column, and cell captions, linked to an HTML Table.

Set-of-Marks Prompting
Set-of-Marks Prompting is a technique used in conjunction with the DETR object detection method to enhance its performance, achieving an IoU score of 18.6.

Accuracy Comparison
Accuracy Comparison refers to the evaluative process in which the perceived accuracy of ChartCitor and GPT-4o is assessed through visual representation in a bar chart.

Bar Chart
The Bar Chart is a visual representation that compares the accuracy perceptions of ChartCitor and GPT-4o across different categories of accuracy.

Claude-3.5
Claude-3.5 employs Sonnet Direct Bbox Decoding and achieved an IoU score of 13.8 in the evaluations.
